{
  "stem": "21786.6",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The uprising simply would be performed in a way that we will use the few primitive weapons we had in different camps, and the gasoline, which will be used to put the wooden barracks aflame.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in the chaos, try to kill some of the SS men, get the weaponry, try to get a hold of some of these guards on the-- on the towers, watch towers.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And try to cause a massive escape, if possible.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was approximately between March and July 1944-- 40-- '44, yes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And also, at one of these trips in Kanada, I met one of the members, by the name of the Zoshek, was his first name.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He belonged-- he was the kapo of the sonderkommando-- special commando which was the commando which handled the gas chambers and the crematoria.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I arranged with him that I was given a supply, a bag of potassium cyanide.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The potassium cyanide, in our primitive pharmacy, we put into this edible paper-like [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] capsules.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I gave it to members of my family, and many friends.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were-- we were successful to make about 25 of these capsules out of the supply.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Simply, our idea was that, should we be in a situation that we are being taken to the gas chambers-- so you just give them the pleasure of biting into the capsule, and that would be it.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I do sincerely hope that my father and my mother-in-law did so, when they went into the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The uprising, [PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] towards the-- at the beginning of June in 1944, they came SS men to the camp.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And everybody went through a selection.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Selection means simply that you marched in front of a group of SS men, usually drunk, extremely abusive.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
